<div id="pf2f7" class="pf w17 hea" data-page-no="2f7"><div class="pc pc2f7 w17 hea"><div class="t m1dff x6c h8c y1d86 ff4 fs31 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">L  </div><div class="t m1e00 x82 h8c y1d86 ff4 fs31 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m1e01 x5e h8c y1731 ff4 fs31 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1</div><div class="t m1e02 x69 h8c y1731 ff4 fs31 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">-4</div><div class="t m1e03 x2d h8c y1082 ff4 fs31 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">:SSOINS </div><div class="t mea1 x6b h13 ybcd ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">—ON THE— </div><div class="t m1e04 x71 h89 y1334 ff2 fs31 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">I </div><div class="t m5 x4a hb3 y1334 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1e05 x64 hb3 y1d98 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&gt;0 0 P </div><div class="t m734 x47 h3e y10c3 ff4 fs17 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">0 P• </div><div class="t m18e9 x2f hb3 y1368 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> TJ I2K </div><div class="t m1322 x37 h22 y11c2 ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">FOR SENIOR </div><div class="t m1d7f x99 h22 y1b5f ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">-</div><div class="t m7e3 x2f h22 y1ea2 ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">CLASSES. </div><div class="t m1e06 x6 h6 y15cf ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ex3r-y- 6 </div><div class="t m181e x31 h13 y11e1 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to. </div><div class="t m4cd x43 h6 y11c3 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">IS,•14ex rc 1-1. 31, </div><div class="t m1e07 x23 h13 y15cf ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1894,. </div><div class="t m319 x66 h31 y13f9 ff1 fs17 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON 1.—January 6, 1894. </div><div class="t m9be x4e h1 y1455 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">JOHN THE BAPTIST&apos;S BIRTH FORETOLD. </div><div class="t m70a x1a h1 ydb5 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 1:1-23. </div><div class="t m4db x14 he y10f3 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THE first four verses of this chapter are introductory. They </div><div class="t m3e3 x3e he y1c2a ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tell why the book was written, to whom it was addressed, and </div><div class="t m66d x3e he yc7f ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the qualifications of the author to write such a treatise. </div><div class="t m59f x14 he y135d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 5-7 introduce and describe Zacharias and his wife </div><div class="t mce2 x3e he y1603 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Elizabeth. </div><div class="t m9af x14 he y1f52 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In verses 8-io we are told what Zacharias was doing when </div><div class="t m5f5 x3e he y1106 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the angel appeared to him; and in verses 11-17 we find a promise </div><div class="t m56f x3e he y11e4 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that a son should be born to Zacharias, and a description of the </div><div class="t m27e x16 he y1cbc ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">work that he should do. </div><div class="t ma66 x14 he y1147 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 18-23 relate the doubt of Zacharias, and the punish-</div><div class="t m8e1 x16 he y1361 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ment for it, and his return to his house. The entire lesson, </div><div class="t m10a x3e he y1190 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">after the introduction, might be summarized thus: The angel </div><div class="t m109 x3e he y12ac ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Gabriel appears to Zacharias, the priest, in the temple, and tells </div><div class="t m15c x16 he y11b8 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">him that he shall have a son, who will be the forerunner of the </div><div class="t m3d3 x16 he y1ca0 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Messiah. The lesson heading is really a sufficient synopsis of </div><div class="t m709 x3e he yf50 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the lesson. </div><div class="t m1048 x73 he y1343 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t mdcb x4e he y1343 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What was the occasion of the writing of the gospel of </div><div class="t m5ab x16 he y1c3c ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke? </div><div class="t m1f3 x73 he y1199 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m265 x4e he y1199 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What were Luke&apos;s qualifications for the work? </div><div class="t m104a x73 he ya21 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t me7 x4e he y1c3d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">To whom was the book addressed ? </div><div class="t mb7 x73 he y156b ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t ma79 x60 he y156b ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What object did Luke have in writing it? </div><div class="t m684 x4c he yd4d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">( 7 ) </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
